.TH "nfc_alloc_send_skb" 9 "nfc_alloc_send_skb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfc_alloc_send_skb \- allocate a skb for data exchange responses
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct sk_buff *" nfc_alloc_send_skb
.BI "(struct nfc_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "struct sock *sk "  ","
.BI "unsigned int flags "  ","
.BI "unsigned int size "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *err "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device sending the response
.IP "sk" 12
socket sending the response
.IP "flags" 12
MSG_DONTWAIT flag
.IP "size" 12
size to allocate
.IP "err" 12
pointer to memory to store the error code
